  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/convert-dms-folder-id-to-name-in-automation/bc-p/14006632#M178792</id>
    <title>Re: Convert DMS Folder ID to Name in Automation</title>
    <updated>2025-02-04T12:11:32.311000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;The above only works if the folder is in the root directory, which is OK for the common scenario of getting the folder ID after a user uploads a file to a trigger form and the process passes the folder ID to an automation.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;To get the path for any folder in the DMS repo, you can simply amend the script task so the URL includes&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;cmis:path&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the &lt;STRONG&gt;filter&lt;/STRONG&gt; query parameter:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;PRE&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;amp;filter=cmis:path,cmis:name&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/PRE&gt;&lt;P&gt;This will return the path of the folder. You can only get this property for a folder.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1738667458850.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/221682iA362521D3D19FE66/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1738667458850.png" alt="Dan_Wroblewski_0-1738667458850.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;P&gt;This property is not returned when you do not filter the request at all.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;You could probably also use the query API call for this.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/convert-dms-folder-id-to-name-in-automation/bc-p/14006632#M178792"/>
    <published>2025-02-04T12:11:32.311000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
