    <title>Re: Convert DMS Folder ID to Name in Automation</title>
    <updated>2025-02-13T19:13:38.211000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Are you saying you have a path of a folder and you need to find the objectId so you can pass it back to the process to put in the approval form?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;You would make a query like this:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-abap"&gt;&lt;code&gt;https://{{endpoint}}/browser/{{repo}}/root/A?filter=cmis:objectId&amp;amp;cmisselector=object&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;P&gt;This returns 4 properties of the folder at that path, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN&gt;cmis:objectId.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I am assuming in your automation your doing some manipulation of documents in your DMS and you are putting documents in all kinds of folders.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-blogs-by-sap/convert-dms-folder-id-to-name-in-automation/bc-p/14016483#M179028"/>
    <published>2025-02-13T19:13:38.211000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
